body:
> error message = 'Permission denied', flags = 13, o_flags = 302

You might want to double check your have admin rights across all drives; it seems you have the program installed on C: (`C:\ProgramData\Anaconda3\envs\DLC-GPU`), but videos on J: (`J:\hello\`) and other things on D: ... (`D:\pytables`)

My guess is you don't have permission to write if J: can you move the video to C: and test again. 


You many also have a similar issue that was reported a year or so ago: 

https://github.com/AlexEMG/DeepLabCut/wiki/Troubleshooting-Tips

> Windows: one user reports an issue with PyTables (i.e. here) pd.read_hdf(path). The solution was to upgrade tables from 3.4.4 to 3.4.5.dev using: `pip install git+https://github.com/PyTables/PyTables`

Hey and thanks for the quick reply! 

This completely solved the issue!
We didn't have writing access on the J drive (Drobo unit). 
Everything is working well now. Thank's a lot! 

Best
Joachim
